    <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
    <div class="meta">
      Last updated: 13 February 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Nexova Digital Solution (CA0417238-V)
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>We want you to be completely satisfied with your purchase. This policy outlines our refund and return procedures for digital products and IT consulting services, in compliance with Malaysia's <strong>Consumer Protection Act 1999</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Digital Products — General Policy</h2>
    <p>Because our products are digital and are delivered immediately upon payment, all sales are generally considered final. However, we do offer refunds in specific circumstances as described below.</p>
    <p>We strongly encourage you to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Read the full product description before purchasing</li>
      <li>Contact us via WhatsApp before purchasing if you have questions about compatibility or features</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. When You ARE Eligible for a Refund</h2>
    <div class="scenario-grid">
      <div class="scenario-card eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-yes">✓ Eligible</div>
        <h3>Product not delivered</h3>
        <p>You paid successfully but did not receive the download link or access credentials within 24 hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-yes">✓ Eligible</div>
        <h3>Significantly different from description</h3>
        <p>The product is materially different from what was described on the product page.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-yes">✓ Eligible</div>
        <h3>Technical defect we cannot fix</h3>
        <p>The product has a critical bug or error that prevents it from functioning as described, and we are unable to provide a fix within 7 business days.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-yes">✓ Eligible</div>
        <h3>Duplicate payment</h3>
        <p>You were charged twice for the same order due to a payment processing error.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>3. When You Are NOT Eligible for a Refund</h2>
    <div class="scenario-grid">
      <div class="scenario-card not-eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-no">✗ Not Eligible</div>
        <h3>Change of mind</h3>
        <p>You changed your mind after purchasing a digital product that was delivered as described.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card not-eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-no">✗ Not Eligible</div>
        <h3>Product already downloaded/accessed</h3>
        <p>The product was successfully delivered and you have already downloaded or accessed it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card not-eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-no">✗ Not Eligible</div>
        <h3>Incompatibility you were aware of</h3>
        <p>The product does not work with a specific tool or platform that was not listed as supported.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card not-eligible">
        <div class="scenario-tag tag-no">✗ Not Eligible</div>
        <h3>Request after 7 days</h3>
        <p>The refund request is made more than 7 days after the purchase date.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4. IT Consulting Services — Refund Terms</h2>
    <h3>Before project commencement:</h3>
    <p>If you cancel before any work has begun, we will refund 100% of any deposit paid.</p>
    <h3>After project commencement:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>If cancelled within 48 hours of commencement: 75% refund of deposit</li>
      <li>If cancelled after work has begun but before 50% completion: 50% refund of deposit</li>
      <li>If cancelled after 50% completion: No refund of deposit; you will receive all completed work</li>
      <li>Final milestone payments are non-refundable once the deliverable has been accepted</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. How to Request a Refund</h2>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
